    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="What is the Star Atlas UE5 Game?" class="article-title">
          What is the Star Atlas UE5 Game?
          
        </h1>

        <div class="article-author">
          
          <div class="article-meta">
            

            <div class="meta-group">
              
                <span class="meta-data"><time datetime="2025-12-09T16:39:34Z" title="2025-12-09T16:39:34Z" data-datetime="relative">December 09, 2025 16:39</time></span>
                <span class="meta-data">Updated</span>
              
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        
          <div class="article-subscribe"><div data-helper="subscribe" data-json="{&quot;item&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/hc/en-us/articles/47210126275347-What-is-the-Star-Atlas-UE5-Game/subscription.json&quot;,&quot;follow_label&quot;:&quot;Follow&quot;,&quot;unfollow_label&quot;:&quot;Unfollow&quot;,&quot;following_label&quot;:&quot;Following&quot;,&quot;can_subscribe&quot;:true,&quot;is_subscribed&quot;:false}"></div></div>
        
      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><figure class="wysiwyg-media"><div data-oembed-url="https://youtu.be/-__WA7izZt4?si=-ca7XHYZoNK450eU"><iframe src="//www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/-__WA7izZt4?si=-ca7XHYZoNK450eU" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" allow="encrypted-media" style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;"></iframe></div></figure><p data-start="357" data-end="720">The <strong data-start="361" data-end="384">Star Atlas Showroom</strong> is the first playable product of Star Atlas built in <strong data-start="438" data-end="457">Unreal Engine 5</strong>, allowing players to interact with the metaverse in full 3D with blockchain-integrated gameplay. It showcases cutting-edge visuals using Nanite and Lumen technologies, and serves as a development hub where new features and play modes are continuously introduced.</p><h3 id="h_01KC1ZNMPQE8AG7NM6SJZT6VY0">&nbsp;</h3><h3 id="h_01KC1ZQ1GVDCRR0CN7VTTZ7RZ9">Choose Your Character</h3><p data-start="131" data-end="267">You no longer play as a preset character. Instead, you can now choose any <strong data-start="205" data-end="220">Crew Member</strong> you own to use as your avatar in the Showroom</p><p data-start="269" data-end="309">There are two ways to get a Crew Member:</p><ul data-start="311" data-end="632">
<li data-start="311" data-end="484" data-list-item-id="efce3a7a9467f5102da12508d0a6b956b"><p data-start="313" data-end="484"><strong data-start="313" data-end="332">Buy a Crew Pack</strong> from the Star Atlas Marketplace and open it to reveal one or more randomized crew<br><a href="https://play.staratlas.com/market/crew/" data-start="422" data-end="482" target="_new" rel="noopener">Browse Crew Packs</a></p></li>
<li data-start="486" data-end="632" data-list-item-id="eed412bbc4b851e40a159badb0d786b45"><p data-start="488" data-end="632"><strong data-start="488" data-end="511">Buy individual Crew</strong> directly on secondary marketplaces like Tensor<br><a href="https://www.tensor.trade/trade/staratlascrew" data-start="566" data-end="632" target="_new" rel="noopener">Buy Crew on Tensor</a></p></li>
</ul><p data-start="634" data-end="724">Once you own a Crew Member, you can select them in-game to represent you in the UE5 world</p><h3 id="h_01KC1ZNMPQ5X07MQPYS77C836W">&nbsp;</h3><h3 id="h_01KC1ZQ1GVGFTJVSNRRWSJXZYH">Main Game Modes Available</h3><h3 id="h_01KC1ZNMPQJEN7Q17VJRHKJ25V" data-start="1065" data-end="1094"><strong data-start="1069" data-end="1094">1. Galia (Open World)</strong></h3><p data-start="1095" data-end="1141">Explore the Showroom’s full galaxy experience:</p><ul data-start="1142" data-end="1312">
<li data-start="1142" data-end="1182" data-list-item-id="ea2cafd471cef6f3314668996aec89881"><p data-start="1144" data-end="1182">Summon your owned ships and fly freely</p></li>
<li data-start="1183" data-end="1229" data-list-item-id="e273408a26e75b2a9ad54ab3048dd04f4"><p data-start="1185" data-end="1229">Navigate to asteroids and <strong data-start="1211" data-end="1229">mine resources</strong></p></li>
<li data-start="1230" data-end="1263" data-list-item-id="e82a02a2f72a9c57bc47e019f8e80a634"><p data-start="1232" data-end="1263">Dock and land at space stations</p></li>
<li data-start="1264" data-end="1312" data-list-item-id="e10a9a3c9f618fc768287229ff82a017b"><p data-start="1266" data-end="1312">Discover new gameplay features added regularly</p></li>
</ul><h3 id="h_01KC1ZNMPQFDAYESDA024ABB5P" data-start="1314" data-end="1338"><strong data-start="1318" data-end="1338">2. Training Mode</strong></h3><p data-start="1339" data-end="1391">Practice and improve your gameplay in solo sessions:</p><ul data-start="1392" data-end="1522">
<li class="ck-list-marker-bold" data-start="1392" data-end="1419" data-list-item-id="e0aba3549ee154107670297985b0496dc"><p data-start="1394" data-end="1419"><strong data-start="1394" data-end="1419">Flight Trainer – Race</strong></p></li>
<li class="ck-list-marker-bold" data-start="1420" data-end="1451" data-list-item-id="e7194c8ee74f9226faaad028bb75d847a"><p data-start="1422" data-end="1451"><strong data-start="1422" data-end="1451">Flight Trainer – Dogfight</strong></p></li>
<li class="ck-list-marker-bold" data-start="1452" data-end="1473" data-list-item-id="ee7c7426dd46015867dfa7474871eaee5"><p data-start="1454" data-end="1473"><strong data-start="1454" data-end="1473">Gunplay Trainer</strong></p></li>
<li data-start="1474" data-end="1522" data-list-item-id="e3f8a597bb4405a9e9425b8e297693c2f"><p data-start="1476" data-end="1522">Other foundational modes to learn the controls</p></li>
</ul><h3 id="h_01KC1ZNMPQJYY8JFX5A3JNC6JE" data-start="1524" data-end="1547"><strong data-start="1528" data-end="1547">3. Fleet Command</strong></h3><p data-start="1548" data-end="1595">Access the SAGE map from within the Showroom</p><ul data-start="1596" data-end="1734">
<li data-start="1596" data-end="1633" data-list-item-id="e27bd44e3e4f0d3505a46888c7bfd76ae"><p data-start="1598" data-end="1633">View the current state of SAGE v0</p></li>
<li data-start="1634" data-end="1734" data-list-item-id="ef93ae124c9b40302544b6cf98f2ffa4c"><p data-start="1636" data-end="1734">See fleets and ships<br><em data-start="1671" data-end="1734"><em>Note: You cannot yet perform SAGE actions from this interface</em></em></p></li>
</ul><h3 id="h_01KC1ZNMPQ6WRMMJ2DVY5DXE7Z" data-start="1736" data-end="1767"><strong data-start="1740" data-end="1767">4. Multiplayer Sessions</strong></h3><p data-start="1768" data-end="1842">Join or host competitive or casual multiplayer matches with other players:</p><ul data-start="1844" data-end="2015">
<li data-start="1844" data-end="1914" data-list-item-id="e884017d4d8773eef2f19d5418c48652a"><p data-start="1846" data-end="1914"><strong data-start="1846" data-end="1878">Surge (Zone Control Gunplay)</strong> – Factions fight to control zones</p></li>
<li class="ck-list-marker-bold" data-start="1915" data-end="1933" data-list-item-id="e8d304fda20e5905fd0443390a8863405"><p data-start="1917" data-end="1933"><strong data-start="1917" data-end="1931">Deathmatch</strong></p></li>
<li class="ck-list-marker-bold" data-start="1934" data-end="1957" data-list-item-id="e8d6c9083fbf5fc51be8beb4252128f4a"><p data-start="1936" data-end="1957"><strong data-start="1936" data-end="1955">Team Deathmatch</strong></p></li>
<li class="ck-list-marker-bold" data-start="1958" data-end="1974" data-list-item-id="e3c2c819c2ad855cccbee3ef0775c4f4a"><p data-start="1960" data-end="1974"><strong data-start="1960" data-end="1972">Gun Game</strong></p></li>
<li class="ck-list-marker-bold" data-start="1975" data-end="1988" data-list-item-id="ebcf05a0391166ea5a43f744b9fdeab93"><p data-start="1977" data-end="1988"><strong data-start="1977" data-end="1986">Zones</strong></p></li>
<li class="ck-list-marker-bold" data-start="1989" data-end="2001" data-list-item-id="e7174591c4f30108c94d648853e65ffc2"><p data-start="1991" data-end="2001"><strong data-start="1991" data-end="1999">Race</strong></p></li>
<li class="ck-list-marker-bold" data-start="2002" data-end="2015" data-list-item-id="eb19eb7817fda006441c393a7d9b00cf7"><p data-start="2004" data-end="2015"><strong data-start="2004" data-end="2015">Explore</strong></p></li>
</ul><h3 id="h_01KC1ZNMPQG3NV158E84H6M0XN">&nbsp;</h3><h3 id="h_01KC1ZQ1GVGCZHPP0MART8C0SY">Features of the Showroom</h3><ul data-start="2145" data-end="2488">
<li data-start="2145" data-end="2215" data-list-item-id="e96c92b36f1a2626d966e4a2233ccd431"><p data-start="2147" data-end="2215">Fully immersive Unreal Engine 5 environment using Nanite and Lumen</p></li>
<li data-start="2216" data-end="2269" data-list-item-id="ea72b1d4ca77d5d3e13b8b9f636f8d924"><p data-start="2218" data-end="2269">Blockchain wallet integration (Solana-compatible)</p></li>
<li data-start="2270" data-end="2328" data-list-item-id="e3835465f7b2d8bedb173c7c05976ad51"><p data-start="2272" data-end="2328">Summon your own NFTs — ships and crew — into the world</p></li>
<li data-start="2329" data-end="2383" data-list-item-id="e7b5a0cd74d01e6442a7c88b988ef5013"><p data-start="2331" data-end="2383">Use a demo ship (Floyd Liner) if you don’t own one</p></li>
<li data-start="2384" data-end="2439" data-list-item-id="e0b0a582771d7cf3b50c0300f8e2d32db"><p data-start="2386" data-end="2439">Integrated <strong data-start="2397" data-end="2411">photo mode</strong> for cinematic screenshots</p></li>
<li data-start="2440" data-end="2488" data-list-item-id="ef177bc76db66d5b55ec71d271653e8f5"><p data-start="2442" data-end="2488">Dynamic lighting, exploration, and easter eggs</p></li>
</ul><p><br>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></div>

          

          
        </div>
      </section>

